<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Sample Blog Post</title>
    <style>
        .parallax-container {
            position: relative;
            overflow: hidden;
            height: 400px;
        }

        .parallax-image {
            position: absolute;
            top: 0;
            left: 0;
            width: 100%;
            height: 100%;
            object-fit: cover;
            transform: translateY(0);
            transition: transform 0.1s ease-out;
        }
    </style>
    <script>
        document.addEventListener("scroll", function() {
            const parallax = document.querySelector(".parallax-image");
            let scrollPosition = window.pageYOffset;
            parallax.style.transform = "translateY(" + scrollPosition * 0.5 + "px)";
        });
    </script>
</head>
<body class="bg-white text-gray-800">
    <div class="container mx-auto py-8 px-4">
        <div class="md:flex md:space-x-8">
            <!-- Left Content Column (2/3 width) -->
            <div class="md:w-2/3">
                <!-- Hero Section with Parallax -->
                <section class="mb-8">
                    <div class="parallax-container mb-4">
                        <img src="https://picsum.photos/1200/400" alt="Hero Image" class="parallax-image rounded-md shadow-md">
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Understanding the Basics of Tailwind CSS</h1>
                        <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
                            <img src="https://picsum.photos/30" alt="Author Avatar" class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full mr-4">
                            <span class="text-gray-600 font-bold">John Doe</span>
                            <span class="text-gray-400 mx-2">•</span>
                            <span class="text-gray-500">August 27, 2024</span>
                            <span class="text-gray-400 mx-2">•</span>
                            <span class="text-gray-500">5 min read</span>
                            <span class="text-gray-400 mx-2">•</span>
                            <span class="text-gray-500">2.3K views</span>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">Tailwind CSS is a utility-first CSS framework that provides low-level utility classes...</p>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <!-- Content Section -->
                <section class="prose lg:prose-xl max-w-none mb-12">
                    <p>Tailwind CSS provides a highly customizable, low-level utility-first framework that allows you to build modern web interfaces rapidly. It offers a suite of utility classes that can be combined to create any design, giving developers full control over their web page designs.</p>
                    <p>Unlike traditional CSS frameworks, which offer pre-designed components, Tailwind CSS is designed to let you create your own components using utility classes that you can style as per your requirement. This makes it highly flexible and ideal for developers who want to customize their UI to a granular level.</p>
                    
                    <!-- Right-aligned Image -->
                    <div class="float-right ml-4 mb-4 w-1/2 p-2">
                        <img src="https://picsum.photos/300/200" alt="Right Aligned Image" class="rounded-md shadow-md w-full">
                    </div>
                    <p>It offers a suite of utility classes that can be combined to create any design, giving developers full control over their web page designs. Unlike traditional CSS frameworks, which offer pre-designed components, Tailwind CSS is designed to let you create your own components using utility classes that you can style as per your requirement. This makes it highly flexible and ideal for developers who want to customize their UI to a granular level.</p>
                    
                    <!-- Left-aligned Image -->
                    <div class="float-left mr-4 mb-4 w-1/2 p-2">
                        <img src="https://picsum.photos/300/200" alt="Left Aligned Image" class="rounded-md shadow-md w-full">
                    </div>
                    <p>With Tailwind CSS, you can apply styles directly in your HTML using utility classes. This method eliminates the need for writing custom CSS, streamlining the development process. Furthermore, Tailwind’s built-in responsive design features make it easier to create designs that work across different screen sizes.</p>
                    
                    <p>Another advantage of Tailwind CSS is its configuration file, which allows you to define your own design system. You can customize colors, spacing, fonts, and more to match your brand’s identity. This ensures that your design remains consistent across your entire website or application.</p>
                </section>

                <!-- Author Bio Section -->
                <section class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-md clear-both">
                    <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
                        <img src="https://picsum.photos/60" alt="Author Avatar" class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full mr-4">
                        <div>
                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">About the Author</h2>
                            <p class="text-gray-600">John Doe is a front-end developer specializing in building responsive and user-friendly web applications.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>
            </div>

            <!-- Right Related Posts Column (1/3 width) -->
            <aside class="md:w-1/3 mt-12 md:mt-0">
